  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali119-kilavi">itu piriviṭai mālaippoḻutu kaṇṭu āṟṟāta talaivi tōḻikku uraittatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali119">
                <l>akaṉñālam viḷakkuntaṉ palkatir vāyākap </l>
                <l>pakaṉuṅki yatupōlap paṭucuṭar kalcēra </l>
                <l>vikaṉmiku nēmiyā ṉiṟampōla viruḷvara </l>
                <l>nilavukkāṇ patupōla vaṇimati yērtarak  </l>
                <l>kaṇpāyal peṟṟapōṟ kaṇaikkā lalarkūmpat </l>
                <l>tampukaḻ kēṭṭārpōṟ ṟalaicāyttu marantuñca </l>
                <l>muṟuvalkoḷ pavaipōla mukaiyaviḻpu putaṉantac </l>
                <l>ciṟuvetirṅ kuḻalpōlac curumpimirn timmeṉap </l>
                <l>paṟavaitam pārppuḷḷak kaṟavaitam pativayiṟ </l>
                <l>kaṉṟamar viruppoṭu maṉṟuniṟai pukutara </l>
                <l>māvati cēra mālai vāḷkoḷā </l>
                <l>vanti yantaṇa retirkoḷa vayarntu </l>
                <l>centīc cevvaḻa ṟoṭaṅka vantatai</l>
                <l>vāliḻai makaḷi ruyirpoti yaviḻkkuṅ</l>
                <l>kālai yāva taṟiyār </l>
                <l>mālai yeṉmaṉār mayaṅki yōrē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>As the setting sun joins the stones as if swallowing the day,</l>
                <l>for a mouth its many rays that illuminated the wide world,</l>
                <l>as darkness crawls up, like the colour of the one with the very hostile discus,</l>
                <l>as the decorative moon rises, like seeing moonlight(?),</l>
                <l>as the round-stemmed blossoms close, like eyes that became sleepy,</l>
                <l>as the trees sleep, bowing [their] heads like people hearing their own praise,</l>
                <l>as the bushes grow by opening buds, as if they were taking on smiles,</l>
                <l>as the bees hum,  like little flutes of bamboo,</l>
                <l>as the birds remember their young ones, as the milk cows in their place</l>
                <l>with desire to abide with [their] calves, enter as a herd the cow shed,</l>
                <l>as animals join [their] lairs, as brahmins, engaged </l>
                <l>in welcoming the dusk that does not take the light of evening,</l>
                <l>start red-flamed red fires, [its] coming</l>
                <l>is called ‘evening’ by those who are confused,</l>
                <l>those who don’t know that it is death/the time,</l>
                <l>which opens the live stores of women with pure jewels.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
